## .NET Performance Analysis: `CaseTransformExtensions.cs`

**Hot paths identified:** `Underscore`, `Pascalize`, `Camelize` (millions of calls)

### Scan Execution Checklist

| Recipe | Hits |
|--------|------|
| `RegexOptions.Compiled` | 7 (3 in `#else`, 3 for `Underscore*`, 1 in `InflectionRule`) |
| `GeneratedRegex` | 3 (only for the `#if NET7_0_OR_GREATER` block) |
| `new Regex(` in constructor | 1 (`InflectionRule`) |
| `.ToLower()` / `.ToUpper()` | 2 (L79, L121) |
| `.Substring(` | 2 (both L79) |
| Chained `Regex.Replace` | 1 (L117-121, triple chain) |
| `sealed class` | 0 of 1 non-static class |

### Positive Patterns

- ✅ `GeneratedRegex` used for 3 patterns under `#if NET7_0_OR_GREATER` — L13, L16, L19
- ✅ `#else` fallback uses `static readonly` + `RegexOptions.Compiled` — correct for pre-.NET 7
- ✅ `IsAllUpperCase` uses `foreach` loop instead of LINQ `.All()` — L159
- ✅ `IsAsciiAlphanumeric` uses `foreach` + `char.IsAsciiLetterOrDigit` — L252
- ✅ `WordCount` uses state-machine `foreach` — no allocations — L276
- ✅ `Slugify` uses `ToLowerInvariant()` — L189

